<p>* Adjustment has been made for the amounts of these securities held outside RBI, since all three are part of the private placement.</p>
<p>Next month the banking system is expected to face a deficit of around 75,000 million rupees, largely on account of the advance tax outflow. We should see a tightening of call money rates towards end March/early April and a downward reaction in prices of gilt edged securities and treasury bills. Hence the next fortnight provides a good opportunity to scale down trading positions ahead of the impending uncertainty.</p>
<p>However, some part of the shortfall of 75,000 million rupees could get offset by the release of funds locked up with the RBI through repo transactions. Secondly, given the bullish sentiment in the equity markets and a consequent rise in foreign portfolio inflows in March could augment the rupee liquidity in the banking system.</p>
